{% set cdn = "https://cdn.circulationstudio.com/clients/laguna-beach-counseling" %}

<main class="ff-guide-page">
  <div class="ff-guide-wrap">

    <header class="ff-guide-masthead">
      <h1>Design lab</h1>
      <p>A working exploration doc, not the finished library. The kept directions per device after review, with real imagery wired in. Gold is reserved for the CTA, the numbered digits, and the pullquote rule. Everything else is teal.</p>
      <span class="ff-guide-note">Internal, noindex, out of sitemap and nav. Nothing here is committed or extracted.</span>
    </header>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 1. KAY PORTRAIT + QUOTE + SIGNATURE                                    #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">01</span>
        <h2>Kay portrait, quote, signature</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Two kept directions. New teal wave eyebrow.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 1 of 2: founder editorial, credential grid</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Authority-forward. Sticky portrait, larger name, a two-column marker grid, and a teal-rule statement block. Grounded in the About page founder treatment.</p>
        <div class="ff-kay ff-kay--founder">
          <div class="ff-kay-portrait ff-kay-portrait--cutout">
            <img src="{{ cdn }}/team/kay-transparent.png" alt="Kay Wenger, LMFT, LPCC, founder of Laguna Beach Counseling" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="ff-eyebrow">Our founder</p>
            <p class="ff-kay-name">Kay Wenger, <em>LMFT, LPCC</em></p>
            <p class="ff-kay-role">Founder</p>
            <div class="ff-kay-body">
              <p>I have spent over 30 years in rooms with people who are anxious, and the pattern is almost always the same. They are trying hard, and the trying is not working. So we stop pushing and get curious instead.</p>
              <p>That is usually where things start to shift. Not with a technique, and not overnight, but with two people looking at the thing together until it gets smaller.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ff-kay-creds">
              <span class="ff-cred">{{ icoCheck | safe }}<span><b>Over 30 years</b> of clinical experience</span></span>
              <span class="ff-cred">{{ icoCheck | safe }}<span><b>LMFT, LPCC</b>, licensed in California</span></span>
              <span class="ff-cred">{{ icoCheck | safe }}<span><b>Out-of-network</b> by design</span></span>
              <span class="ff-cred">{{ icoCheck | safe }}<span><b>Laguna Beach</b> or telehealth</span></span>
            </div>
            <div class="ff-kay-statement">
              <p>You're not stuck because something's wrong with you. The alarm is real, the danger usually is not, and we work on helping it tell the difference again.</p>
              <cite>Kay Wenger, LMFT, LPCC</cite>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 2 of 2: centered note, portrait on top</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">The most intimate. A small round portrait above a centered quote and note, on a warm sand card. Reads like a personal note rather than a bio.</p>
        <div class="ff-kay--note">
          <div class="ff-kay-note-portrait">
            <img src="{{ cdn }}/team/kay-transparent.png" alt="Kay Wenger, LMFT, LPCC" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          </div>
          <p class="ff-eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">A note from Kay</p>
          <p class="ff-kay-quote">You're not stuck because <em>something's wrong with you.</em></p>
          <div class="ff-kay-body">
            <p>They are trying hard, and the trying is not working. So we stop pushing and get curious instead. That is usually where things start to shift, with two people looking at the thing together until it gets smaller.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ff-kay-sign">
            <span class="ff-kay-sign-name">Kay Wenger</span>
            <span class="ff-kay-sign-role">LMFT, LPCC, Founder</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Portrait ground treatments (behind the cutout only)</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Three ways to treat the ground behind the transparent portrait. Motion is scoped to the portrait frame only, never the text column. Turn on Reduce Motion to confirm treatment 2 freezes to the same frame as treatment 1.</p>
        <div class="ff-kayground-compare">
          <figure>
            <div class="ff-kay-portrait ff-kayground">
              <img src="{{ cdn }}/team/kay-transparent.png" alt="Kay Wenger portrait cutout on a sea-foam ground" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            </div>
            <figcaption>1: static + grounding shadow<span>Sea-foam wash plus a soft contact shadow beneath the figure. No motion.</span></figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <div class="ff-kay-portrait ff-kayground ff-kayground--anim">
              <img src="{{ cdn }}/team/kay-transparent.png" alt="Kay Wenger portrait cutout on a slowly drifting sea-foam ground" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            </div>
            <figcaption>2: subtle animated wash<span>The same ground with a very slow, low-amplitude drift on the wash layer. Barely perceptible.</span></figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <div class="ff-kay-portrait ff-kayground ff-kayground--frozen">
              <img src="{{ cdn }}/team/kay-transparent.png" alt="Kay Wenger portrait cutout on a static sea-foam ground" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            </div>
            <figcaption>3: reduced-motion fallback (same as 1)<span>Treatment 2 with motion forced off, the single static frame a reduced-motion viewer sees.</span></figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 2. ASYMMETRIC SPLIT                                                    #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">02</span>
        <h2>Asymmetric split, text and image</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Three compositions kept.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 1 of 3: text left, image right, near-even</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">The anxiety page baseline. A gentle 1.02 to 0.98 asymmetry, pullquote (gold rule) closing the text column.</p>
        <div class="ff-split">
          <div class="ff-split-text">
            <p class="ff-eyebrow">What is really happening</p>
            <h3 class="ff-h2">Your alarm is working. <em>It is just set too sensitive.</em></h3>
            <p class="ff-desc">If you're here, some part of your day has probably started to organize itself around worry. The 3 a.m. replay of a conversation. The meeting you rehearse twenty times. The plans you quietly turn down. Anxiety is a smoke detector that has grown a little too sensitive, going off for burnt toast as loudly as for a real fire.</p>
            <p class="ff-desc">The alarm is real. The danger usually isn't. So how do we help it tell the difference again? That's usually where we start, and you don't have to sort it out alone.</p>
            <p class="ff-pullquote">That's not a character flaw. That's just how the nervous system works.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ff-imgframe">
            <img src="{{ cdn }}/services/therapy/parent-teenoutdoors.jpeg" alt="A parent and teen walking outdoors together, relaxed and unhurried" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 2 of 3: flipped, image-dominant</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Image on the left and larger (a stronger 1.18 to 0.82 split), text on the right ending in a text link. Grounded in the Beach Therapy flipped split.</p>
        <div class="ff-split ff-split--image ff-split--flip">
          <div class="ff-split-text">
            <p class="ff-eyebrow">A different setting</p>
            <h3 class="ff-h2">Anxiety often eases when you're <em>moving.</em></h3>
            <p class="ff-desc">Some people find it easier to breathe, in both senses, walking the coastline than sitting across a desk. Beach Therapy is the same real work, outdoors and side by side, with the ocean doing a little of the talking.</p>
            <p class="ff-beach-anchor">Sometimes the environment matters.</p>
            <a class="ff-btn-text" href="/beach-therapy">Explore Beach Therapy {{ icoArrowThin | safe }}</a>
          </div>
          <div class="ff-imgframe ff-imgframe--wide">
            <img src="{{ cdn }}/beach-therapy/beach-walk-frombehind.jpeg" alt="Two people walking side by side along the Laguna shoreline, seen from behind" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 3 of 3: overlap composition</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Image and text layer rather than sit side by side. A floating paper card overlaps the image over a soft sea-foam wash. Pullquote scaled down to sit in proportion with the card.</p>
        <div class="ff-overlap">
          <div class="ff-overlap-media">
            <div class="ff-imgframe ff-imgframe--wide">
              <img src="{{ cdn }}/coastal/crescent-bay-cove.jpeg" alt="A wide, calm view of Crescent Bay Cove on the Laguna coastline" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ff-overlap-card">
            <p class="ff-eyebrow">What is really happening</p>
            <h3 class="ff-h2" style="font-size:clamp(1.6rem,2.6vw,2.2rem);">Your alarm is working. <em>It is just set too sensitive.</em></h3>
            <p class="ff-desc" style="margin-bottom:0;">Anxiety is a smoke detector that has grown a little too sensitive, going off for burnt toast as loudly as for a real fire. The alarm is real. The danger usually isn't.</p>
            <p class="ff-pullquote">That's not a character flaw. That's just how the nervous system works.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 3. ICON-TILE CARD                                                     #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">03</span>
        <h2>Icon-tile card</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Selected direction: centered, circular badge, teal hairline.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Selected direction: centered, circular badge, teal hairline</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">A calm, formal card. Larger circular icon, centered text, a thin teal top rule as the only accent.</p>
        <div class="ff-cards">
          <article class="ff-card ff-card--center">
            <span class="ff-card-icon">{{ icoWave | safe }}</span>
            <h3>The worry loop</h3>
            <p>The relief lasts about a minute before the next what-if arrives. The loop feels productive. Mostly it's exhausting.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="ff-card ff-card--center">
            <span class="ff-card-icon">{{ icoHeart | safe }}</span>
            <h3>The body's alarm</h3>
            <p>Your body is running a threat response built for lions, not inboxes. Nothing is broken.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="ff-card ff-card--center">
            <span class="ff-card-icon">{{ icoCompass | safe }}</span>
            <h3>The avoidance trap</h3>
            <p>Avoidance works for an afternoon, then the world quietly shrinks. It is a loan with a very high interest rate.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 4. GOLD-RULE PULLQUOTE                                                #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">04</span>
        <h2>Gold-rule pullquote</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Selected direction: centered editorial, gold tick above.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Selected direction: centered editorial, gold tick above</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">A short centered gold tick opens it (the deliberate gold accent) and an attribution closes it, set on a soft sea-foam wash so it reads as a calm breath between the busier card sections.</p>
        <div class="t-foam ff-foam-panel">
          <blockquote class="ff-pullquote ff-pullquote--center">
            <span class="ff-pullquote-tick" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            That's not a character flaw. That's just how the nervous system works.
            <span class="ff-pullquote-attr">Kay Wenger, LMFT, LPCC</span>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 5. STACKED SEO CARD PATTERN                                           #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">05</span>
        <h2>Stacked SEO card pattern</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Selected direction: numbered divider list, gold digits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Selected direction: numbered divider list</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Hairline dividers with a serif-italic index number in gold, for a quiet, editorial list. Grounded in the brand guidelines numbered pillars.</p>
        <ul class="ff-forms ff-forms--numbered">
          <li class="ff-form">
            <span class="ff-form-index" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
            <span class="ff-form-icon">{{ icoHeart | safe }}</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Panic attacks</h3>
              <p>Panic disorder is the fear of the next one. Panic is treatable, and understanding what's happening is often the first turn.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="ff-form">
            <span class="ff-form-index" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
            <span class="ff-form-icon">{{ icoShield | safe }}</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Phobias</h3>
              <p>Fear that has narrowed onto one specific thing. Treatment works in steps small enough to stay with, until the fear loosens its grip.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="ff-form">
            <span class="ff-form-index" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
            <span class="ff-form-icon">{{ icoChat | safe }}</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Social anxiety</h3>
              <p>We work on the beliefs underneath it, and practice, gently, until connection feels less like a performance.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 6. PILL-LINK ROW                                                      #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">06</span>
        <h2>Pill-link row</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Selected direction: sand pills, icon and label.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Selected direction: sand pills, icon and label</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">The anxiety page baseline. Soft sand chips with a small teal icon.</p>
        <div class="ff-pills">
          <a class="ff-pill" href="/therapy/individuals">{{ icoCompass | safe }}Individual therapy</a>
          <a class="ff-pill" href="/telehealth">{{ icoChat | safe }}Online therapy in California</a>
          <a class="ff-pill" href="/beach-therapy">{{ icoWave | safe }}Beach Therapy</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 7. TRUST BAND                                                         #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">07</span>
        <h2>Trust band</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Selected direction: navy ground, gold-light accents.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ff-guide-variant">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Selected direction: navy ground, gold-light accents</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">Four markers on a navy band with gold-light icons, for a bolder near-hero moment. Uses the a11y-safe gold-on-navy pairing.</p>
        <div class="ff-trust ff-trust--navy">
          <div class="ff-trust-inner">
            <p class="ff-trust-lead">Starting is the part people dread. <em>Here is how it actually goes.</em></p>
            <div class="ff-trust-grid">
              <div class="ff-trust-item">
                {{ icoClock | safe }}
                <span><b>{{ site.access.seenWithin }}</b><span>Reach out today and we will get back to you quickly.</span></span>
              </div>
              <div class="ff-trust-item">
                {{ icoChat | safe }}
                <span><b>A free first call</b><span>A relaxed 15 to 20 minute Get to Know Us call, before anything else.</span></span>
              </div>
              <div class="ff-trust-item">
                {{ icoShield | safe }}
                <span><b>Out-of-network by design</b><span>Full-length sessions, real confidentiality, and Superbills for your PPO.</span></span>
              </div>
              <div class="ff-trust-item">
                {{ icoWave | safe }}
                <span><b>{{ site.nap.addressLocality }} or telehealth</b><span>In person on Third Street, or by secure video anywhere in California.</span></span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ===================================================================== #}
    {# 8. FINAL CTA BAND WITH WATERMARK                                      #}
    {# ===================================================================== #}
    <section class="ff-guide-block">
      <div class="ff-guide-block-head">
        <span class="ff-guide-num">08</span>
        <h2>Final CTA band with watermark</h2>
        <p class="ff-guide-block-note">Two grounds kept. Tagline set as a quiet closing line.</p>
      </div>

      {#
        CONSTRAINT: this navy variant must NOT be the last section directly above
        the footer. The footer is navy too, so navy-on-navy makes a low-contrast
        seam. Use the sand-warm variant (below) immediately before the footer.
      #}
      <div class="ff-guide-variant ff-guide-variant--tall">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 1 of 2: navy ground, centered watermark</p>
        <p class="ff-guide-var-desc">A giant faint Together watermark centered behind centered copy and one gold CTA. Note: do not place this navy variant directly above the navy footer.</p>
        <div class="ff-final">
          <div class="ff-final-inner">
            <h3>There's a way <em>through this.</em></h3>
            <p>If anxiety has been running the show, let's talk. A free 15 to 20 minute call is a low-pressure way to see whether we're the right fit for you.</p>
            <a class="ff-btn-gold" href="{{ site.booking.getStartedPath }}">
              {{ site.booking.navLabel }}
              <span class="ff-btn-gold__arrow">{{ icoArrow | safe }}</span>
            </a>
            <p class="ff-final-tagline">{{ site.tagline }}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {# This sand-warm variant is the footer-safe one: it reads clearly against
         the navy footer, so this is the variant to place immediately before it. #}
      <div class="ff-guide-variant ff-guide-variant--tall">
        <p class="ff-guide-var-label">Variation 2 of 2: sand ground, navy-tinted watermark</p>
